amage. This book is a vivid, richly detailed account of a distinctive landscape and its occupants, revealing the push–pull of local and expert knowledge and the role of the state in the postwar era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFlood dams and reservoirszFundy, Bay of, RegionxHistory. 0aFlood dams and reservoirs. 0aReclamation of landzFundy, Bay of, RegionxHistory. 0aReclamation of land. 0aSalt marsheszFundy, Bay of, RegionxHistory. 0aSalt marshes. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh1 aWynn, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311141764640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486677440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774866774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774866774/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-141764-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles